{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":901,"text":"The informal markets of Africa\nare stereotypically seen"},{"time":4856,"text":"as chaotic and lackadaisical."},{"time":7234,"text":"The downside of hearing\nthe word \"informal\""},{"time":9911,"text":"is this automatic grand\nassociation we have,"},{"time":12604,"text":"which is very negative,"},{"time":14254,"text":"and it's had significant consequences\nand economic losses,"},{"time":18787,"text":"easily adding -- or subtracting --\n40 to 60 percent of the profit margin"},{"time":24297,"text":"for the informal markets alone."},{"time":27157,"text":"As part of a task of mapping\nthe informal trade ecosystem,"},{"time":31483,"text":"we've done an extensive literature review"},{"time":34040,"text":"of all the reports and research\non cross-border trade in East Africa,"},{"time":39015,"text":"going back 20 years."},{"time":40850,"text":"This was to prepare us for fieldwork\nto understand what was the problem,"},{"time":45208,"text":"what was holding back informal trade\nin the informal sector."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49990,"text":"What we discovered\nover the last 20 years was,"},{"time":53518,"text":"nobody had distinguished\nbetween illicit --"},{"time":57295,"text":"which is like smuggling or contraband\nin the informal sector --"},{"time":61764,"text":"from the legal but unrecorded,"},{"time":64128,"text":"such as tomatoes, oranges, fruit."},{"time":67697,"text":"This criminalization --"},{"time":70041,"text":"what in Swahili refers to as \"biashara,\"\nwhich is the trade or the commerce,"},{"time":75263,"text":"versus \"magendo,\" which is\nthe smuggling or contraband --"},{"time":78721,"text":"this criminalization\nof the informal sector,"},{"time":82266,"text":"in English, by not distinguishing\nbetween these aspects,"},{"time":86159,"text":"easily can cost each African economy\nbetween 60 to 80 percent addition"},{"time":91776,"text":"on the annual GDP growth rate,"},{"time":94568,"text":"because we are not recognizing the engine"},{"time":98326,"text":"of what keeps the economies running."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100924,"text":"The informal sector is growing jobs\nat four times the rate"},{"time":104425,"text":"of the traditional formal economy,"},{"time":106391,"text":"or \"modern\" economy, as many call it."},{"time":108972,"text":"It offers employment and income\ngeneration opportunities"},{"time":112462,"text":"to the most \"unskilled\"\nin conventional disciplines."},{"time":116183,"text":"But can you make a french fry\nmachine out of an old car?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120403,"text":"So, this, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":123888,"text":"is what so desperately needs\nto be recognized."},{"time":127128,"text":"As long as the current assumptions\nhold that this is criminal,"},{"time":131410,"text":"this is shadow,"},{"time":132661,"text":"this is illegal,"},{"time":134303,"text":"there will be no attempt at integrating\nthe informal economic ecosystem"},{"time":138787,"text":"with the formal or even the global one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142968,"text":"I'm going to tell you a story of Teresia,"},{"time":145796,"text":"a trader who overturned\nall our assumptions,"},{"time":149896,"text":"made us question all the stereotypes\nthat we'd gone in on,"},{"time":153270,"text":"based on 20 years of literature review."},{"time":157675,"text":"Teresia sells clothes under a tree\nin a town called Malaba,"},{"time":163188,"text":"on the border of Uganda and Kenya."},{"time":165876,"text":"You think it's very simple, don't you?"},{"time":168810,"text":"We'll go hang up new clothes\nfrom the branches,"},{"time":171491,"text":"put out the tarp, settle down,\nwait for customers,"},{"time":174447,"text":"and there we have it."},{"time":175816,"text":"She was everything we were expecting\naccording to the literature,"},{"time":179225,"text":"to the research,"},{"time":180517,"text":"right down to she was a single\nmom driven to trade,"},{"time":184318,"text":"supporting her kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187092,"text":"So what overturned our assumptions?"},{"time":189726,"text":"What surprised us?"},{"time":191269,"text":"First, Teresia paid the county\ngovernment market fees"},{"time":195015,"text":"every single working day"},{"time":196870,"text":"for the privilege of setting\nup shop under her tree."},{"time":200147,"text":"She's been doing it for seven years,"},{"time":202222,"text":"and she's been getting receipts."},{"time":204560,"text":"She keeps records."},{"time":206061,"text":"We're seeing not a marginal,"},{"time":209252,"text":"underprivileged,"},{"time":210623,"text":"vulnerable African woman trader\nby the side of the road -- no."},{"time":216463,"text":"We were seeing somebody\nwho's keeping sales records for years;"},{"time":220586,"text":"somebody who had an entire ecosystem\nof retail that comes in from Uganda"},{"time":226931,"text":"to pick up inventory;"},{"time":229270,"text":"someone who's got handcarts\nbringing the goods in,"},{"time":233156,"text":"or the mobile money agent\nwho comes to collect cash"},{"time":236096,"text":"at the end of the evening."},{"time":237548,"text":"Can you guess how much\nTeresia spends, on average,"},{"time":241980,"text":"each month on inventory --"},{"time":244601,"text":"stocks of new clothes\nthat she gets from Nairobi?"},{"time":247819,"text":"One thousand five hundred US dollars."},{"time":250525,"text":"That's around 20,000 US dollars\ninvested in trade goods and services"},{"time":255989,"text":"every year."},{"time":257568,"text":"This is Teresia,"},{"time":259042,"text":"the invisible one,"},{"time":260463,"text":"the hidden middle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262442,"text":"And she's only the first rung\nof the small entrepreneurs,"},{"time":266559,"text":"the micro-businesses that can be found\nin these market towns."},{"time":270674,"text":"At least in the larger Malaba border,\nshe's at the first rung."},{"time":276523,"text":"The people further up the value chain"},{"time":279183,"text":"are easily running\nthree lines of business,"},{"time":282252,"text":"investing 2,500 to 3,000\nUS dollars every month."},{"time":287772,"text":"So the problem turned out\nthat it wasn't the criminalization;"},{"time":291776,"text":"you can't really criminalize someone\nyou're charging receipts from."},{"time":296957,"text":"It's the lack of recognition\nof their skilled occupations."},{"time":303048,"text":"The bank systems and structures\nhave no means to recognize them"},{"time":307068,"text":"as micro-businesses,"},{"time":308580,"text":"much less the fact that, you know,"},{"time":311182,"text":"her tree doesn't have\na forwarding address."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313912,"text":"So she's trapped in the middle."},{"time":316262,"text":"She's falling through the cracks\nof our assumptions."},{"time":318717,"text":"You know all those microloans\nto help African women traders?"},{"time":322646,"text":"They're going to loan her\n50 dollars or 100 dollars."},{"time":325500,"text":"What's she going to do with it?"},{"time":327130,"text":"She spends 10 times\nthat amount every month"},{"time":329496,"text":"just on inventory --"},{"time":331122,"text":"we're not talking about\nthe additional services"},{"time":333433,"text":"or the support ecosystem."},{"time":335864,"text":"These are the ones who fit\nneither the policy stereotype"},{"time":339476,"text":"of the low-skilled and the marginalized,"},{"time":341904,"text":"nor the white-collar,\nsalaried office worker"},{"time":344799,"text":"or civil servant with a pension"},{"time":346684,"text":"that the middle classes\nare allegedly composed of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350080,"text":"Instead, what we have here\nare the proto-SMEs"},{"time":354656,"text":"these are the fertile seeds\nof businesses and enterprises"},{"time":358475,"text":"that keep the engines running."},{"time":360442,"text":"They put food on your table."},{"time":362201,"text":"Even here in this hotel,\nthe invisible ones --"},{"time":365298,"text":"the butchers, the bakers\nthe candlestick makers --"},{"time":368774,"text":"they make the machines\nthat make your french fries"},{"time":371191,"text":"and they make your beds."},{"time":372441,"text":"These are the invisible businesswomen\ntrading across borders,"},{"time":377037,"text":"all on the side of the road,"},{"time":379430,"text":"and so they're invisible\nto data gatherers."},{"time":382704,"text":"And they're mashed together\nwith the vast informal sector"},{"time":386384,"text":"that doesn't bother to distinguish\nbetween smugglers and tax evaders"},{"time":391481,"text":"and those running illegal whatnot,"},{"time":394113,"text":"and the ladies who trade,"},{"time":396168,"text":"and who put food on the table\nand send their kids to university."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400337,"text":"So that's really what I'm asking here."},{"time":403586,"text":"That's all that we need to start by doing."},{"time":406868,"text":"Can we start by recognizing\nthe skills, the occupations?"},{"time":411501,"text":"We could transform the informal economy\nby beginning with this recognition"},{"time":416149,"text":"and then designing the customized\ndoorways for them to enter"},{"time":420854,"text":"or integrate with the formal,"},{"time":423087,"text":"with the global,"},{"time":424415,"text":"with the entire system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426150,"text":"Thank you, ladies and gentlemen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427738,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}